<subSubSection id="B0CE3A8BFFAAFF8E15E8F30807F2FE8F" box="[197,1269,311,338]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F86B6900FFAAFF8E15E8F30807F2FE8F" blockId="36.[151,1436,152,418]" box="[197,1269,311,338]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="CAA0B512FFAAFF8E15E8F308024DFE8C" bold="true" box="[197,330,311,337]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Etymology</emphasis>
. This species is named for Queen Cleopatra of 
<collectingCountry id="80C32990FFAAFF8E165BF30700C7FE8F" box="[886,960,312,338]" name="Egypt" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Egypt</collectingCountry>
. It is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B0CE3A8BFFAAFF8E15E8F36003FAFE7F" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="distribution">
